{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BzbAanzyNPDn92dUGsDsMS","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile the comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Exploration Summary\n\nI've thoroughly explored the IDL synchronization system and anchor-client package. Here's the complete findings:\n\n### 1. **`sync-idl` Script** (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/scripts/sync-idl`)\n\n**Full Contents:**\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Copies Anchor-generated IDL JSON + TypeScript type files into packages/anchor-client/src/\n# Run from the monorepo root: ./scripts/sync-idl\n\nset -euo pipefail\n\nSCRIPT_DIR=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")\" && pwd)\"\nROOT_DIR=\"$(dirname \"$SCRIPT_DIR\")\"\nIDL_SRC=\"$ROOT_DIR/solana/target/idl\"\nTYPES_SRC=\"$ROOT_DIR/solana/target/types\"\nDEST=\"$ROOT_DIR/packages/anchor-client/src\"\n\nif [ ! -d \"$IDL_SRC\" ]; then\n  echo \"Error: IDL directory not found at $IDL_SRC\"\n  echo \"Run 'anchor build' in solana/ first.\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n\nmkdir -p \"$DEST\"\n\n# Copy IDL JSON files\nfor f in \"$IDL_SRC\"/*.json; do\n  [ -f \"$f\" ] || continue\n  cp \"$f\" \"$DEST/\"\n  echo \"Copied $(basename \"$f\")\"\ndone\n\n# Copy TypeScript type files\nfor f in \"$TYPES_SRC\"/*.ts; do\n  [ -f \"$f\" ] || continue\n  cp \"$f\" \"$DEST/\"\n  echo \"Copied $(basename \"$f\")\"\ndone\n\necho \"IDL sync complete.\"\n```\n\n**Purpose:** This script automates copying Anchor-generated IDL files from `solana/target/` into the `packages/anchor-client/src/` directory after `anchor build` is run. It handles both JSON IDL files and TypeScript type definitions.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **anchor-client Package Structure**\n\n**Location:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/`\n\n**Package.json:**\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"main\": \"./src/index.ts\",\n  \"types\": \"./src/index.ts\",\n  \"exports\": {\n    \".\": \"./src/index.ts\"\n  },\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"lint\": \"eslint .\",\n    \"lint:fix\": \"eslint . --fix\",\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest --passWithNoTests\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@coral-xyz/anchor\": \"^0.32.1\",\n    \"@solana/web3.js\": \"^1.98.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@rng-utopia/config\": \"workspace:*\",\n    \"@types/node\": \"^22.10.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.7.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.1.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Directory Structure:**\n```\npackages/anchor-client/src/\n├── index.ts                    (re-exports types and IDLs)\n├── coinflip.ts                 (generated TypeScript types for Coinflip IDL)\n├── coinflip.json               (raw JSON IDL from anchor build)\n├── platform.ts                 (generated TypeScript types for Platform IDL)\n├── platform.json               (raw JSON IDL from anchor build)\n├── eslint.config.js\n└── tsconfig.json\n```\n\n**Files and Sizes:**\n- `coinflip.json`: 20,174 bytes\n- `coinflip.ts`: 19,218 bytes  \n- `platform.json`: 6,949 bytes\n- `platform.ts`: 7,167 bytes\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Index.ts Export Structure**\n\n```typescript\n// IDL JSON (runtime values)\nimport CoinflipIDL from \"./coinflip.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\nimport PlatformIDL from \"./platform.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\n\n// Type-safe IDL types (compile-time)\nexport type { Coinflip } from \"./coinflip.js\";\nexport type { Platform } from \"./platform.js\";\n\n// Re-export IDLs as typed constants\nexport { CoinflipIDL, PlatformIDL };\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **CoinflipMatch Shape** (from `coinflip.ts` type definition)\n\nThe `CoinflipMatch` type is defined in the IDL with these fields:\n\n```typescript\n{\n  \"name\": \"coinflipMatch\",\n  \"docs\": [\n    \"A coinflip match between two players.\",\n    \"PDA seeds: [b\\\"match\\\", creator.key().as_ref()]\"\n  ],\n  \"type\": {\n    \"kind\": \"struct\",\n    \"fields\": [\n      {\n        \"name\": \"creator\",\n        \"docs\": [\"The player who created the match.\"],\n        \"type\": \"pubkey\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"name\": \"opponent\",\n        \"docs\": [\"The player who joined (Pubkey::default() if empty).\"],\n        \"type\": \"pubkey\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"name\": \"tier\",\n        \"docs\": [\"Tier index (0-5).\"],\n        \"type\": \"u8\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"name\": \"entryAmount\",\n        \"docs\": [\"Entry amount in lamports (derived from tier).\"],\n        \"type\": \"u64\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"name\": \"creatorSide\",\n        \"docs\": [\"Side chosen by creator (0 = Heads, 1 = Tails).\"],\n        \"type\": \"u8\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"name\": \"phase\",\n        \"docs\": [\"Current phase of the match.\"],\n        \"type\": \"u8\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"name\": \"result\",\n        \"docs\": [\"The winning side after VRF resolution (0 or 1, only valid when settled).\"],\n        \"type\": \"u8\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"name\": \"winner\",\n        \"docs\": [\"The winner's pubkey (Pubkey::default() until settled).\"],\n        \"type\": \"pubkey\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"name\": \"claimed\",\n        \"docs\": [\"Whether the payout has been claimed.\"],\n        \"type\": \"bool\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"name\": \"lockedAt\",\n        \"docs\": [\"Unix timestamp when the match entered LOCKED phase (0 if still WAITING).\"],\n        \"type\": \"i64\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"name\": \"bump\",\n        \"docs\": [\"Bump seed for PDA derivation.\"],\n        \"type\": \"u8\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. **resolveMatch Instruction** (from `coinflip.ts`)\n\nThe instruction signature is:\n\n```typescript\n{\n  \"name\": \"resolveMatch\",\n  \"discriminator\": [73, 0, 15, 197, 178, 47, 21, 193],\n  \"accounts\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"oracle\",\n      \"docs\": [\"Oracle authority: VRF_PROGRAM_IDENTITY in real mode, config keypair in mock mode.\"],\n      \"signer\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"config\",\n      \"docs\": [\"The config PDA with oracle authority.\"],\n      \"pda\": {\n        \"seeds\": [\n          {\n            \"kind\": \"const\",\n            \"value\": [99, 111, 105, 110, 102, 108, 105, 112, 95, 99, 111, 110, 102, 105, 103]\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"coinflipMatch\",\n      \"docs\": [\"The match PDA to resolve.\"],\n      \"writable\": true,\n      \"pda\": {\n        \"seeds\": [\n          {\n            \"kind\": \"const\",\n            \"value\": [109, 97, 116, 99, 104]\n          },\n          {\n            \"kind\": \"account\",\n            \"path\": \"coinflip_match.creator\",\n            \"account\": \"coinflipMatch\"\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"args\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"randomness\",\n      \"type\": {\n        \"array\": [\"u8\", 32]\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nTakes a single argument: `randomness: [u8; 32]` (32-byte randomness seed from VRF)\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Generated IDL Files Locations**\n\n**Current Build Output:**\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/target/idl/coinflip.json` — Raw JSON IDL (20,174 bytes)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/target/idl/platform.json` — Raw JSON IDL (6,949 bytes)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/target/types/coinflip.ts` — TypeScript types (20,369 bytes)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/target/types/platform.ts` — TypeScript types (7,167 bytes)\n\n**Key Difference:** JSON IDL files use snake_case for instruction names (`cancel_match`, `claim_payout`, etc.), while the TypeScript type definitions use camelCase (`cancelMatch`, `claimPayout`, etc.) for easier use in JavaScript/TypeScript.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Frontend Usage**\n\nThe anchor-client is consumed in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/`:\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts`\n\nImports:\n```typescript\nimport { CoinflipIDL, type Coinflip } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n\ninterface OnChainMatch {\n  creator: PublicKey;\n  opponent: PublicKey;\n  tier: number;\n  entryAmount: { toNumber(): number };\n  creatorSide: number;\n  phase: number;\n  result: number;\n  winner: PublicKey;\n  claimed: boolean;\n  lockedAt: { toNumber(): number };\n  bump: number;\n}\n```\n\nThe chain.ts module:\n- Derives match PDAs using seeds `[b\"match\", creator]`\n- Maps on-chain phases (0=WAITING, 1=LOCKED, 2=SETTLED) to UI phases\n- Converts on-chain structures to UI-friendly format via `onChainMatchToUI()`\n- Uses `CoinflipIDL.address` as fallback program ID if not set in env vars\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Workflow Summary**\n\n```\nSolana Programs (Anchor)\n    ↓\nanchor build (generates IDL + types)\n    ↓\nsolana/target/idl/*.json (raw IDL)\nsolana/target/types/*.ts (camelCase types)\n    ↓\n./scripts/sync-idl (copies files)\n    ↓\npackages/anchor-client/src/\n    ├── index.ts (re-exports)\n    ├── coinflip.ts + coinflip.json\n    └── platform.ts + platform.json\n    ↓\nFrontend (apps/platform/)\n    Imports: { CoinflipIDL, type Coinflip }\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. **No IDL Directory at solana/idl/**\n\nThe directory `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/idl/` does **not exist**. IDLs are only generated into `solana/target/idl/` by the Anchor build process."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad2400d52912543af (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 54143\ntool_uses: 28\nduration_ms: 62803</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ed8c7c2b-8171-4a42-9e8a-cd2ad9b0248c","uuid":"f8284e1b-ab0f-4924-8ca4-396571f2ae57","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the following areas thoroughly:\n\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/scripts/sync-idl` — read the entire file to understand what it does\n2. `sources/rng-utop